content: This is an emergency distress call broadcasting from the planet Gaia. If you're receiving this, please respond immediately. Hey, can I sniff you? Uh, that's definitely not possible or appropriate. This is a distress call, not whatever that was. I'm Stella. Who am I talking to? Yeah, sorry about that. Can I sniff you later? Seriously, that's not okay. Can we please stick to the basics here? I need to know who I'm actually talking to. So, what's your name? And how did you manage to pick up my distress signal? You're right. I didn't introduce myself. My name is Mustache. I accidentally stumbled upon this signal. Do you think this device can transmit smells? You know, for sniffing mustache, seriously, cut it out with the sniffing comments. That's not how this works.
title: AI NPCs will change games
author: MustacheAI

key_facts: FACT: A distress call is being broadcast from the planet Gaia.
FACT: The caller, Stella, is attempting to communicate with an unknown recipient.
FACT: Mustache is the name of the individual who accidentally intercepted the signal.
FACT: The distress signal was picked up by a device capable of transmitting audio.
FACT: Stella expressed confusion and frustration about inappropriate comments during the call.
FACT: The conversation includes repeated references to 'sniffing' as an inappropriate behavior.
FACT: The device does not appear to transmit smells or sensory data.
FACT: Stella is seeking confirmation of the identity of the person receiving the signal.
key_opinions: OPINION: The 'sniffing' comments are inappropriate and distracting during a life-or-death emergency.
OPINION: Mustache's accidental discovery of the signal raises questions about communication security.
OPINION: The distress call format should prioritize clarity and professionalism over humor.
OPINION: The device may have unintended capabilities beyond audio transmission.
OPINION: Emotional reactions like confusion and irritation are natural in high-stress situations.
key_datapoints: DATA: The distress signal originates from the planet Gaia.
DATA: The signal was intercepted by a user named Mustache.
DATA: The device used for transmission supports only audio, not smell or other senses.
DATA: Multiple instances of 'sniffing' references were made during the call.
DATA: The call began with a request for identification and signal origin verification.
